criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. patients with Chronic limb-threatening ischemia (CLTI);

          2. patients voluntary and capable of follow-up;

          3. patients > 18 years of age;

          4. informed consent.

        Definition of CLTI:

          1. the presence > 2weeks duration;

          2. arteriosclerosis is related;

          3. ankle-brachial index (ABI) < 0.4, absolute highest ankle arterial pressure <50 mmHg,
             absolute toe arterial pressure <30 mmHg, transcutaneous partial pressure of oxygen
             (TcPO2) < 30 mmHg.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Contraindication for antiplatelet , anticoagulant or thrombolytic agent;

          2. Contrast agent allergy;

          3. Dysfunctional protein C, protein S, antithrombin Ⅲ(AT Ⅲ) or refusal of blood
             transfusion;

          4. Life expectancy < 12 months;

          5. Interventional treatment was adopted to the target artery within 1 year;

          6. Elective operation is to be performed within 30 days except surgical intervention in
             this clinical study;

          7. Participation in other clinical study;

          8. Complications affecting surgical safety;

          9. Chronic Kidney Disease(CKD);

         10. Major amputation was adopted to the target extremity;

         11. The existence of aneurysm in the target vessels;

         12. The existence of perforation, dissection or any other injury requiring intervention in
             the target vessels.
